ATTR: condition: good#cylinders: 4 cylinders#drive: 4wd#fuel: gas#odometer: 189000#paint color: green#title status: clean#transmission: automatic
MESSAGE: 2000 subaru outback limited. it has the classic subaru rear fender rust. 189;000 miles on the car. however; the motor is a different story.#i bought the car from a large used car lot in freeport. six months after purchase the motor spun a rod bearing. onto the next motor; a 140;000 mile motor from a large auto dismantler in edgerton; wi. ran perfect until one week past the warranty. the car sat for 8 months. one day i woke up; looked out the window at the car and said ok; time to get this thing back on the road.#i dismantled the motor completely. bought a new subaru crank; rod & main bearings; timing belt and water pump; head gaskets; and all other gaskets needed to reassemble. the car has been running fine since then. 19;000 miles and no issues. motor and trans are good. brand new lower radiator hose. brand new resonator pipe.#the bad. the side panel for the passenger side door fell off at 20mph. i have it; i just havent bothered to try to re-attach it. and possibly one new rear rotor (other one is new with 4 miles on it). the leather interior has seen better days. drivers side is worn. rear seat has a lot of scratch marks in it. passenger seat has a puncture hole in it from me dropping a drill onto it.#i wouldnt hesitate to trek across the country with it. a little tlc and you have a great reliable car! heat is hot; ac is cold...and yes they both work. battery is about 1.5 years old. awd works great.#trades? maybe. possibly a ford ranger. maybe a motorcycle. be realistic with trade offers. i dont want your 70s cafe racer that got the ass end chopped off and a duct tape pillow for a seat!

MESSAGE: selling my subaru outback.  its been my daily driver for 3 or 4 years now.  its always been reliable and ran well.  recently it overheated on me and i took it to a mechanic a few days later.  on the short drive to and from the mechanic it was also trying to overheat on me so i havent been driving it.  the mechanic told me it needed a new water pump as well as a few other repairs he advised i get while he was in there; including timing belt.  he told me that would likely fix the overheating and he didnt see any obvious leaks in the radiator.  the bill wasnt gonna be cheap and i cant afford anything beyond routine maintenance so im forced to sell.  we talked for quite a while after i told him this and he advised i look for a buyer willing and capable of doing the repairs themselves; anyone who knows the car should have no trouble.  i looked up the parts and theyre fairly cheap; it was the labor that was gonna hurt me; and i dont have the knowledge to do it myself.#it had new tires in 2015; theyre worn but should be good for a while.  ive had some repairs in the last year or so and found a lot of my receipts; including brakes and rotors in november; some front end suspension repairs; and a misfiring plug in january along with a pretty thorough inspection.  i have that paperwork as well for an interested buyer to look over.  it may need a battery because it needs to be jumped to drive; but that could be a couple other issues instead.  up until the overheat it ran and drove great; but at the moment it cant travel far without risk.  brand new tags; cleaned it up; decent stereo deck but stock speakers.  slow leak in front right tire; probably just needs a patch.  front bumper has some damage on driver side; also missing that side fog light; neither is essential and has been driving a couple years as is.  myself and previous owner both dog owners; i vacuumed it really well but stubborn traces remain.  was not a smoker; however.  could probably stand to have an alignment once its up and running.#i dont want anyone to get a bad deal so if youre not interested in working on this yourself or putting the money in for repairs id advise you to look elsewhere but its been a great car for me and id love to keep it if i knew what i was doing.  i think someone with the skill set could get a lot more miles out of it and id love to see it go to a good home.#please text me if youre interested; MESSAGE: i have a 2005 subaru outback for sale. i have not been driving it lately because it seems to have a bit of an exhaust leak. it seems like it only happens after warm up and when waiting at intersections. the car has a manual transmission which is in fantastic condition. but with this kind of turbo vehicle (and the fact its all-wheel drive) its best to rev match when down shifting. i love this wagon; its crazy fast but i need a more reliable vehicle as a daily driver. when i bought the car it ran fine then the turbo shaft broke when i parked the car on a hill (didnt know better at the time). so i replaced the turbo with an ebay turbo. the turbo makes good boost. as far as trouble codes i got p2096 for post catalyst fuel trim system too lean. i had the passenger front cv joint replaced with oem cv joint by a mechanic. i have replace the tgv sensor on bank 1; which is right in front of the turbo. i have not got any codes related to the tgv since replacing the sensor. but the mechanic who replaced my cv joint said that an exhaust leak is most likely to cause the p2096 code. basically if you can tighten the turbo to the up-pipe and down-pipe better than i have you (and start saving for the turbo you want to put in it like a borg warner) you will have an amazing turbo wagon.

MESSAGE: 2007 subaru outback ll bean edition h6 3.0 6 cylinder wagon. i am the second owner of this vehicle and it has spent its whole life in utah. this car is very clean underneath. no rust compared to a midwest vehicle. i bought this car with around 100;000 miles and planned to drive it past 300;000. i babied this car and wanted to have it forever. i changed to oil no later than 3;000 miles with royal purple full synthetic. it has never burned oil. air filter cleaned and changed regularly. cabin air filter replaced last fall. brakes front and rear less than a year ago. the tires are general grabber at2 with about 30;000 miles. they have a 60;000 tread life warranty. i purchased the tires to have good winter traction while not being as soft as a snow tire. i treated this thing like i was going to have it forever; but i need something to tow and did not want do anything to wreck my subaru. this is the h6 3 liter engine which is not prone to head gasket issues like the 2.5 engine in most outback! it also has a timing chain; so no costly timing belt service or headache! i have also had the airbag recall performed; so it will not launch metal parts at you any longer. despite the desert rust free life the car is ten years old and is not show room perfect. the front bumper is missing the tow receiver cover and has some cracking and paint chips. the chips are all on plastic and will not be an issue with rusting. the front driver seat has a rip in the leather. the rip has been there for 50;000 miles and has not grown at all. i noticed a leak in the power steering on my drive from utah. i used lucas oil powersteering fluid and the leak seems to be very slow. pulleys; seals are brand new and oem.#new windshield#new turbocharger#new shocks and mounts#new exedy high performance clutch and flywheel#new vacuum lines; pcv lines; air intake hoses (because rubber hoses get brittle with age)#newer tires (about 3000 miles on them)#new brakes including brake fluid flush#new alternator#new powersteering pump#new differential fluid front and rear#new belts#new thermostat#new transmission mounts#aligned#no check engine lights. all sensors functioning normally. no wheel bearing noises.#problems:   these 4 things are everything that i know and none threaten your wallet.#1) sometimes pops out of reverse gear.  transmission was removed; opened and inspected by a subaru transmission specialist at soobie surgeons in hudson wisconsin.  he is a subaru master mechanic.  i hired him to find and fix the problem since i was unable to find anything wrong on the outside.  in a nutshell he removed the transmission and did a complete tear down and was not able to find anything wrong with it.  his words its totally pristine.  he double checked all the mounts and linkages and couldnt explain the problem but says it has nothing obviously wrong and no sign of impending failure.    i can provide his number but you can also google the name above - the numbers are all in the book.#2) there is a crack in the plastic cover of the turn signal light on the right side mirror.  this component does not have a replacement part so would need to replace the entire mirror.  i did not do this but it the repair is simple for the diyer.  most likely you wouldnt know it if it wasnt pointed out.#3)  there is a rust hole in the back exhaust pipe with a patch.  does not affect vehicle but patches do loosen over time which will make it louder sounding.  a muffler shop or mechanic with welding ability can put weld a patch on quite inexpensively.#4)  there is a stripped stud between exhaust downpipe and rear resonance pipe (part of exhaust) - does not affect the exhaust system but over time it will get an exhaust leak here.  like 3 it is a cheap and easy fix at any muffler shop.#thats about it.  this car is in excellent condition and stick shift turbo outbacks are very hard to find.  usually if you want a stick turbo you need to downsize into the impreza line (which are awesome cars too but they are smaller and tighter and less family friendly).#last:  i need this car sold and gone and price is negotiable.

TITLE: 98 subaru outback
ATTR: fuel: gas#odometer: 239283#title status: clean#transmission: automatic
MESSAGE: $1500 or best offer!!#ive had this car since i was 16 years old; so its been my trusty sidekick for 11 years. its taken me across the country and back; to many ca national parks; and back and forth to sacramento once or twice per month. honestly; id love to keep this car forever; but i have neither the energy nor ambition to bring this car up to its full potential (and i just bought a new car). as the gaines family would say; this car is a fixer upper!#pros:#beautiful body--i love this model of this car and im sad they dont make cars like this anymore.#leather seats- unfortunately the drivers seat is a little torn up (see picture); and im not sure how that happened.#all wheel drive!#roomy#it runs#great on flat roads!#never been in an accident!!!-there are a few scratches (see pictures); but this is due to people backing into my car or swiping it; and not leaving a note!#opportunities for improvements:#no ac- hasnt had ac since i bought it in 2006; but luckily the bay never gets too hot. its unbearable in sacramento heat; though.#slow oil leak- this leak has also been there since 2006; but my mechanics have said theres no reason to fix it if i dont need to because its slow enough that there is still plenty of oil left when i get my oil changed at 5000miles.#one new tire-unfortunately; i got a flat tire a few weeks before i bought my new car; and didnt want to put in the money to get all 4 new tires. because its an awd; its important that all the tires are the same tread because it could potentially mess up the awd...but to be honest; since 2012; ive always had one tire that was different than the others because i got a flat tire on my cross country road trip; and no one has said that my alignment is messed up.#struggles up hills- i avoid marin ave and havent taken it up to tahoe in a long time. i avoid hills because it smokes going up hills (due to the slow oil leak). this apparently is an issue for all subarus of this year; but my mechanic also says that the 98s are way better than the 2000s. buuuuuut; its great on flat roads :-d#miles--over 239;000 miles; but subarus are immortal (thats why i bought a crosstrek!)#speedometer--sometimes it wont work until you hit 40.#cd player doesnt work---but who listens to cds anymore; anyway? (okay; i totally do; but my life has been fine without it).#i recognize this is a long post; but i want this beast to go to a good home; whilst being honest about what it needs. if you are someone who loves cars; this is the perfect opportunity to make this car brand new again.#let me know if youd like to come see it; test drive it; or simply ask questions about it. i will be camping saturday and sunday; so im sorry if i dont respond until monday!

TITLE: 30th anniversary edition subaru legacy outback sus
ATTR: condition: good#cylinders: 4 cylinders#drive: 4wd#fuel: gas#odometer: 165000#paint color: red#size: compact#title status: clean#transmission: automatic#type: sedan
MESSAGE: this car came to me from my brother who purchased it from a lady that thought it was going to blow up or catch on fire due to some oil leakage ! the car had some failed seals and gaskets that fortunately allowed oil to blow out instead of in therefore the oil did not mix with coolant or gas only leaked out onto motor and exhaust system which caused a lot of smoke when the vehicle was beimg driven thus giving her the idea that it was all over since smoke usually means fire or something of the like! well after having the motor cleaned up and inspected by a certified mechanic the main seals and gaskets along with timing belt water pump and head gaskets where all replaced and the car has not given me a single problem for the 2 years i have owned it!! subarus are famous for blowing head gaskets for many many years due to a very minimal internal fuel leak that every single one of their 4cyl motors has and when the car is not being driven that small amount of gasoline in the oil starts to break down the seals and gaskets from the inside causing gasket and seal failure. this car luckily had external failure so no internal parts where damaged or affected by the issue and the fact that it was repaired and inspected rite at the time of the failure the car never got a chaance to have a major malfunction or breakdown!! the timing belt and waterpump were replaced only due to the oil leakage that got them covered in oil and we felt it best to replace those to prevent any future problems just incase plus the mechanic was already taking the motor apart to replace gaskets it just made sence to do the extra to make sure i didnt have another situation ! so that is the bottom line on this car! the other issues this car has is driverside rear window glass not the actual window in door the one between door and rearwindow is nolonger inplace the paint is getting signs of age and use but still shines up real nice! the carpet behind driver had a paint can spill but is comoletely covered by the floor mat and finally after all the work done the car has a very small oil leak rite above the exhaust system crossover it is a loose or damaged seal for the oil cooling system. its like a coupler or joiner for the line to carry the oil out of engine and through the cooler and it only leaks at a stop not while running? strange but it is just something that happens due to rocks or debris on road thst bounces off underside of vehicles during daily driving . the car has never failed me not once it has gone back and forth to los angeles and lake forest a handful of times and is a very strong running vehicle ! it has never overheated nor has it become hotter than normal driving temp even on hot dsys ! the transmission is strong as well no issues ever with slow or slip shifting ! i have maintained this vehicle very very well always using pennzoil and the appropriate additives for both trans and engine as well as power stearing just to keep it all working well and keeping it lubed and tuned daily!! the tires are at half life and show no signs of irregular wear and tear they are uniform and in good shape ! the interior is a 7-7 1/2 out of 10 ans the exterior is a 7 out of 10! the car runs and drives like it should no issues or hesitation ever!! passed smog last may no problem and is current on registration and insurance! this is a very dependable vehicle and safe . never had any accidents and actually doesnt have bad style even with its age! cloth interior no rips or tears or stains minus the paint spill! front driverside fender has small dent but overall very clean straight body! this car will last another 10-15 years if maintained the way i have done with no major issues as the gasket problem has already been addressed! daily driver for anybody and gas milage is better than average and still has plenty of get up and go!! anything i havent mentioned feel free to ask or come take a look and drive for yourself! its not something amazing but it is a great car!! i am selling it so i can catch up on rent and bills as i hsve been out of work for 2 years now due to injury to my lower back and leg. i also cant afford to insure 2 vehicles and gas when im not working still! if i didnt use my truck so much i would sell it and keep the car but i need my little truck more than the car so here it is! i can honestly say im a truck guy and never hsve owned a small car like this before but i am so impressed with this subaru that i would purchase another one no question!! these are safe dependable cars and i would let my son drive one without any worry these are one of the best vehicles i have ever owned!!!
